Former Ekiti State Governor Ayo Fayose has urged Ekiti people to reject the All Progressives Congress (APC) and vote for the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) at the June 18, 2022 Governorship poll. Fayose made this remark while leading the Campaign Trail of the PDP governorship candidate, Honourable Bisi Kolawole to major areas in Ado-Ekiti, the state capital. The two-term Ekiti State governor of Ekiti State expressed optimism that PDP will take the State back to the path of progress that it was before the APC snatched power from it in 2018. He also lamented the high level of insecurity in the State, linking it to an alleged nonchalant attitude of the APC government. The PDP leader said: “Ekiti State was already messed up by the APC government, but as usual, PDP will fix the Amongst the areas visited were, Apata Natha, Nova and Aba Igbira areas of Ado Ekiti. Kolawole, who was accompanied by his running mate, Barrister Kolapo Kolade and other PDP leaders, was described as “the perfect man to bring smiles to the faces of Ekiti people who are under the burden of a governor that is not accessible to even his party men.” In his address  Kolawole, who promised to take the welfare of the people as his topmost priority if elected as governor, said having lived in the midst of the Ekiti people for over 20 years, he understood their plights and will address them accordingly. POLL Apparently referring to Governor Kayode Fayemi, Kolawole said he will not operate like a diaspora governor and that he will be a governor that Ekiti can see and feel.